This paper is primarily focused on the study of quantum finite automata, which is a topic in formal language theory (FL). The paper discusses the computational power of multi-letter QFAs, which is a topic in computational complexity (CC). The paper also discusses the equivalence of QFAs, which is a topic in both discrete structures (DS) and logic in computer science (LO). Finally, the paper discusses the time complexity of determining equivalence, which is a topic in electronic and computer engineering (ET).
